@lisalendway #tcltk is for writing GIUs for code running on your own machine.

So if that's all you want (or you want to give a script to someone else to run in R on their machine), then tcltk can help.

THe problem, as I'm finding, is that tcltk is an ugly pain in the a$$.

#RStats

#tcltk conceptual difficulty: 

* All elements *must* be assigned a parent when created.
* But this does not mean that the element is positioned within the parents layout.
* A completely separate layout command must be done !

#RStats https://t.co/csEfLnTRHg

1-to-1 mapping between TCL<->R, + parent required at creation time, lead to *3* separate funcs just to place element in window:

1. create an object with a parent
2. pack the object within the parent
3. configure how the object is packed within the parent
